=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
The target is a complex polycyclic aromatic heterocycle with an OH attached to aromatic carbon. We need propose immediate precursors and disconnection. Likely disconnection of C-O bond forming phenol via electrophilic aromatic substitution? Could be from a protected phenol (e.g., O-alkyl) then deprotection. But immediate precursor set maybe a phenol precursor with leaving group (e.g., O-OTf) and a nucleophile? Actually retrosynthesis: break the C-O bond to give a phenoxide and a leaving group? Could propose precursor as the same aromatic core with O-OTf (triflate) and then nucleophilic substitution with OH-? But more plausible is that the phenol can be formed by oxidation of a phenyl ether (e.g., demethylation). So immediate precursor: the same core with O-CH3 (anisole) and then demethylation to phenol. So disconnection: cleavage of C-O bond to give anisole precursor and OH- (or H+). But they ask immediate precursors (set) and disconnection description. So answer: anisole (methoxy) version of target as precursor; disconnection: O-methyl cleavage (demethylation) to

